<InfoPage
  title="Conference Rules"
  intro="A few guidelines to help us steward this time together well."
>
  <h2>Spirit of the Gathering</h2>
  <p>
    This is a School of the Spirit — a sacred time set apart for prayer,
    worship, and encounter. Come with a heart ready to receive and to give.
  </p>

  <h2>Phones & Devices</h2>
  <p>
    Keep phones on silent during sessions. Be present with the people and the
    moment in front of you.
  </p>

  <h2>Accommodation</h2>
  <p>
    Rooms are assigned — please stay in your assigned room. Men's and
    women's accommodation are kept separate.
  </p>

  <h2>Meals</h2>
  <p>
    One meal a day is provided at the times announced on-site. Please be
    punctual — food may not be held for latecomers. Inform the welfare team of
    any food allergies or dietary requirements on arrival.
  </p>

  <h2>Dress Code</h2>
  <p>Smart Casual throughout the conference.</p>

  <h2>Conduct</h2>
  <p>
    Please follow all instructions from the Camp Commandant and staff, and
    attend every session.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Don't stay behind in the dorm to sleep while a session is holding.</li>
    <li>Don't arrive late to sessions.</li>
    <li>
      We are sharing dormitories with other people — don't pray loudly in the
      room while others are sleeping.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Children & Families</h2>
  <p>
    Parents/guardians are responsible for supervising their children at all
    times, including during sessions and in shared/dorm spaces.
  </p>

  <h2>Personal Belongings</h2>
  <p>
    Bring your own towel, blanket, and toiletries. Keep valuables with you or
    secured — the conference is not responsible for lost or stolen items.
  </p>

  <h2>Health & Safety</h2>
  <p>
    Inform the Camp Commandant immediately of any medical condition,
    medication, or emergency.
  </p>

  <h2>Departure</h2>
  <p>Please do not leave the venue without informing the Camp Commandant.</p>
</InfoPage>
